message.content: One of the most significant events that happened in Slovakia in the past 5 years is the murder of journalist Ján Kuciak and his fiancée Martina Kušnírová in February 2018. This shocking event had a major impact on Slovak society and led to widespread protests against corruption and a lack of transparency in the country. The murder prompted a political crisis that eventually led to the resignation of then-Prime Minister Robert Fico and his government. This event sparked a larger movement for change and reforms in Slovakia's political and judicial systems.
